data.meta_description: Olympic Champion. Richard Andrew Johnson was an American archer. He competed in the Olympic Summer Games five times. He was part of the 1996 American team that won the gold medal that year in the Atlanta games. He also won a team bronze in 2000 at the Sydney Summer Games.
